<p>	Q.  What was going through your mind at the end of the game shooting those free throws?</p>
<p>	Q.  After you were having a tough game shooting the basketball, it seems you went to your floor game and you had a lot of steals, a lot of assists in the ballgame; talk about that? </p>
<p>	Q.  Could you talk about the catch on that last play before you were fouled; it seemed like the most difficult part of that play?</p>
<p>	Q.  What was going through your mind when that free throw was bouncing off the rim? </p>
<p>	Q.  This was probably as close  -- I mean, I know the politically correct thing is to say this is a team victory, but this was as close to a single-handed show as we've seen here.  Can you talk about taking over this game? </p>
<p>	Q.  Can you talk about what was going through your head before the free throws at end with 5.9 seconds left?</p>
<p>	Q.  Talk about where all three of you were on defending the last possession for Purdue? </p>


<p>	Q.  I know there has been a lot of talk this year about how Notre Dame has been a more balanced team, where in years past it was maybe Ruth and four other people on the court but Kelley and Niele; can you talk about how fitting it was that it was Ruth on the line at the end? </p>
<p>	Q.  Your ankle looked a little tender in the warmups, but it did not seem to affect you during the game? </p>
<p>	Q.  The lob to Ruth, what did you think of the release, how good of a pass and how good of a catch was it?</p>
<p>	Q.  Could you describe the foul?  What did Shereka do to hinder you on the play that you went to the line? </p>
<p>	Q.  Yes.</p>
<p>	Q.  Throughout the game, did you feel like you were dominating the game?  Did you feel like you could do what you wanted to do and get it to go where you wanted?</p>

